WEBVTT

00:13:58.030 --> 00:14:01.133
But what if people started out
cooperating in the first round?

00:14:01.593 --> 00:14:05.101
It turned out they made a smooth shift
to competing in the second round.

00:14:05.514 --> 00:14:08.339
They naturally adopted a pattern
of friendly rivalry,

00:14:08.363 --> 00:14:11.593
where they tried to beat each other
but not to undermine each other.

00:14:12.275 --> 00:14:14.860
So think about what that means
for your own rivalries.

00:14:14.884 --> 00:14:17.482
(Music)

00:14:17.506 --> 00:14:20.196
Your early interactions
can cast a long shadow.

00:14:20.603 --> 00:14:22.852
When you first come across
some new competitors,

00:14:22.876 --> 00:14:24.897
you might try getting off
on the right foot

00:14:24.921 --> 00:14:28.118
by complimenting their work
or even inviting them to collaborate.

00:14:29.150 --> 00:14:31.164
If you want to build a supportive rivalry,